   343	       (`Store.submit` never clears the claim on success), so
   344	       `WrongToken` rules out "we won and the response was lost."
   345	     - `InvalidPrecondition` → form re-render (400) with the
   346	       wire-error banner, NOT an orphan. The operator can fix
   347	       the metrics and resubmit; orphaning a fixable form
   348	       failure would be hostile UX.
   349	   - **Read-back-required failures** (skip remaining retries,
   350	     jump to the read-back block below):
   351	     - `IllegalTransition` — the store raises this when
   352	       `task.state` is not in `{"claimed", "submitted"}` at
   353	       call time. After a transport-indeterminate first attempt,
   354	       the task may be `pending` (sweeper reclaimed → we lost),
   355	       `completed` / `failed` (orchestrator already terminalized
   356	       → we won), or `submitted` by another claimant
   357	       (conflict). The read-back distinguishes these. **This is
   358	       a deliberate departure from the chunk-9c implementer
   359	       module's short-circuit pattern**, which mis-classifies a
   360	       lost-response-then-orchestrator-terminalization as an
   361	       orphan; see §K-2 for the parallel fix needed in 9c.
   362	   - **Transport-shaped exceptions** (any `Exception` not in the
   363	     four above) are retried with backoff; on exhaustion, jump
   364	     to the read-back block.
   365	3. **Read-back block.** `store.read_task(task_id)` +
   366	   `store.read_submission(task_id)` + `submissions_equivalent`.
   367	   Decisions:
   368	   - `task.state == "claimed"` and `task.claim.token == our token`
   369	     → orphan `recovery_kind="auto"` ("transport failure;
   370	     retry safe — claim still ours, sweeper will reclaim eventually").
   371	   - `task.state == "claimed"` but our token is gone → orphan
   372	     `recovery_kind="auto"` (`eden://error/wrong-token`) — same
   373	     prose; the prior reclaim already invalidated us.
   374	   - `task.state in {"submitted", "completed", "failed"}`:
   375	     - `read_submission` returns `None` → orphan
   376	       `recovery_kind="transport"` ("store invariant violation").
   377	       Implementation-illegal but defensively handled.
   378	     - `submissions_equivalent(prior, our)` → success page (200).
   379	       (Note: `EvaluateSubmission` equivalence keys off
   380	       `status + trial_id + metrics`; `artifacts_uri` is **not**
   381	       part of equivalence per chapter 04 §4.2 + the
   382	       `submissions_equivalent` impl. The first submission's
   383	       `artifacts_uri` wins.)
   384	     - non-equivalent → orphan `recovery_kind="conflict"`
   385	       (`eden://error/conflicting-resubmission`).
   386	   - `task.state == "pending"` → orphan `recovery_kind="auto"`
   387	     ("task reclaimed before our submit committed; retry safe by
   388	     re-claiming the task").
   389	   - `read_task` itself raises → orphan
   390	     `recovery_kind="transport"` (read-back probe failure).
   391	
   392	### §C-rationale — why `IllegalTransition` is not a definitive short-circuit
   393	
   394	`Store.submit` raises `IllegalTransition` when
   395	`task.state ∉ {"claimed", "submitted"}` at the moment of the call
   396	(`reference/packages/eden-storage/src/eden_storage/_base.py` ~L593).
   397	After the route's first transport-indeterminate `submit` call, the
   398	task may have moved to:
   399	
   400	- `completed` / `failed` — our prior call committed and the
   401	  orchestrator's terminal transition fired. Read-back finds an
   402	  equivalent recorded submission → success.
   403	- `pending` — the sweeper reclaimed our claim before our prior
   404	  call committed. Read-back finds no submission → orphan auto.
   405	- `submitted` by *another* worker (vanishing race) — read-back
   406	  finds a non-equivalent submission → conflict.
   407	
   408	Treating `IllegalTransition` as a definitive orphan would
   409	mis-classify the first case (we won) as an orphan. The simplest
   410	correct fix is to route `IllegalTransition` into the read-back
   411	arm where the actual outcome is determined.
   412	
   413	`WrongToken` and `ConflictingResubmission` *are* definitive:
   414	`WrongToken` requires `task.state == "claimed"` with a
   415	non-matching token (which never happens after a successful prior
   416	submit, because successful submit preserves our token), and
   417	`ConflictingResubmission` is the spec-specified definitive
   418	"different payload won" signal.
   419	
   420	The single-step structure means there's no Phase-1-failed /
   421	Phase-2-failed split. The submit either succeeds, definitively
   422	fails (rendered as a form error or orphan), or transport-fails
   423	into the read-back arm.
   424	
   425	### §C-recovery (per-error)
   426	
   427	| Outcome | Definition | UI rendering | Operator action |
   428	|---|---|---|---|
   429	| ok | submit returned cleanly OR retry returned cleanly OR read-back found equivalent prior submission | `evaluator_submitted.html`, 200 | none |
   430	| InvalidPrecondition (form-time, e.g. metric type drift only the server caught) | server rejected the metrics shape | re-render draft with the wire-error banner attached | fix the metrics and resubmit |

